## Database Schema (Phase 2)

> [!NOTE]
> **Database Implementation Details**
> 
> The following schema will be implemented in Phase 2. Tables include:
> 
> - `workshops` - Workshop event data
> - `music_instruments` - Instrument catalog
> - `music_levels` - Skill levels per instrument
> - `music_packages` - Package plans
> - `monthly_announcements` - Schedule announcements
> - `users` - Student information
> - `orders` - Purchase records
> - `registrations` - Workshop registrations
> - `memberships` - Music lesson package subscriptions
> - `refunds` - Refund processing records

High-level schema structure (detailed ERD to be created in Phase 2):

```sql
-- Workshop tables
workshops (id, title, subtitle, cover_image, description, instructor_id, date, location, capacity_total, capacity_remaining, price, registration_deadline, status, created_at, updated_at)

workshop_galleries (id, workshop_id, image_url, order)

instructors (id, name, bio, avatar, created_at)

-- Music tables
music_instruments (id, name, cover_image, description, contains_equipment, equipment_description, rental_available, rental_offset_allowed, created_at)

music_levels (id, instrument_id, name, order)

music_packages (id, level_id, name, lesson_count, bonus_lessons, valid_duration_months, first_class_date, formation_required, formation_decision_days, refund_policy, price, status, created_at)

monthly_announcements (id, month, instrument_id, schedule_data, announcements, created_at)

-- User & Order tables
users (id, email, name, phone, created_at)

orders (id, user_id, order_type, item_id, amount, payment_status, payment_method, transaction_id, created_at)

workshop_registrations (id, order_id, workshop_id, user_id, status, created_at)

music_memberships (id, order_id, package_id, user_id, valid_from, valid_until, lessons_remaining, status, created_at)

refunds (id, order_id, reason, amount, status, processed_at, created_at)
```

---

## API Endpoints (Phase 2)

RESTful API structure using Next.js API routes:

**Workshops:**
- `GET /api/workshops` - List all published workshops
- `GET /api/workshops/:id` - Get workshop detail
- `POST /api/workshops/:id/register` - Register for workshop
- `POST /api/admin/workshops` - Create workshop (admin)
- `PUT /api/admin/workshops/:id` - Update workshop (admin)
- `DELETE /api/admin/workshops/:id` - Delete workshop (admin)

**Music:**
- `GET /api/music/instruments` - List all instruments
- `GET /api/music/instruments/:id` - Get instrument with levels/packages
- `GET /api/music/announcements/:month` - Get monthly schedule
- `POST /api/music/packages/:id/purchase` - Purchase package
- `POST /api/admin/music/instruments` - Create instrument (admin)
- `POST /api/admin/music/packages` - Create package (admin)
- `POST /api/admin/music/announcements` - Create announcement (admin)

**Orders & Payment:**
- `POST /api/orders` - Create order
- `GET /api/orders/:id` - Get order status
- `POST /api/payment/process` - Process payment
- `POST /api/payment/refund` - Process refund (admin)

